IBADAN – Engr. Seyi Makinde has offi­cially declared his intention to recontest as the executive Gov­ernor of the pacesetter state come 2013 general election. Makinde, the incumbent governor of Oyo State made known his intention on Thurs­day via his verify social media page. Makinde posted on his Face­book wall that he has picked up the expression of interest and nomination forms to run for a term in office. The content of the post as obtained the Saturday INDE­PENDENT read as thus: “In my newsletter today, I an­nounced that I have picked up the Expression of Interest and Nomination forms for a second term as the elected Governor of the good people of Oyo State. If the good people of Oyo State desire it, we will serve for four more years.” Makinde was elected into the office of Governor of Oyo State on March 9 2019 having defeated Chief Bayo Adelabu, the All Progressive Congress (APC) candidate at the guber­natorial elections. He officially took the man­tle of Oyo leadership from the former governor, Late Senator Isiaq Abiola Ajimobi on May 29 2019 having Sworn-In as the 28th executive Governor of the state by the state Chief Judge, Justice Munta Abimbola at the historical Obafemi Awolowo Stadium, (Liberty Stadium) Oke Ado Ibadan.